title: October Spooky Patch - Braids + Rings + Eventide Harmonizer
description:
2 separate arpeggiators feeding into CVPal.  Low part is Braids into Ripples into DVCA.  Envelope created by Peaks and fed into Shades, then combined with LFO and modulating Ripples Freq.     Sequence fed into Harmonizer on Black Hole preset, 100% wet.

High part is Rings directly into DVCA ch 2, enveloped by Peaks ch 2.  Additional reverb from Valhalla Shimmer and a bit of delay from Native Instruments Replika.

Gates for both channels going into SSSR Labs VC Divider with divisions modulated by VCLFO.  Out from VC Divider into Branches for more gate randomness.

title: Sunday and Coffee.  Ambient self-generating patch
description:
PATCH NOTES:

I'm terrible at patch notes, but here goes:

VCDLFO sending triggers to Peaks and clocking Ornament & Crime on Trig 1.
Ornament and Crime in Quantermain mode.  Peaks trigger filtered by Branches probability at about 75%.

Voice 1:
Channel A with Turing Machine CV source to DVCA Channel 1 to narrow the voltage range.  DVCA back into O_c quantizing the incoming CV on Channel B.  Resultant CV send to Braids in 3 sawtooth mode.
Braids out into Ripples LP4 VCA.  Peaks sending ADSR to Ripples VCA.  Ripples out into Mixer ch. 1.

Voice 2:
Channel C with Turing Machine CV source and clock division to +4 to DVCA Channel 2.  DVCA back into O_c quantizing the incoming CV on Channel D.  Resultant CV send to Z3000. z3000 sine out to mixer channel 2.

Mixer to Rosie.

Modulation:

Blue Lantern LFO sending very slow LFO to Shades ch3.  Attenuated to reduce the range and send to Ripples Freqency for slow filter modulation.

Small about of reverb provided by Toraverb and a healthy amount of delay from NI Repika.

title: Hazy Morning - Improvised Eurorack Performance
description:
Patch Notes:

Melody:
O_c Turing Machine, 4 steps, quantized to Dm 
Ch A - Braids -- Ripples LP4 VCA -- Clouds (Parasites) -- Mixer ch 1.
Blue Lantern LFO modulating Braids Timbre slowly.
VCDLFO Sine -- MI Shades -- Ripples Freq modulation. VCDLFO CV is narrowed quite a bit by Shades, so the LFO modulation range is smaller and more subtle.

Bass:
O_c Turing Machine, 16 steps, quantized to Dm, clock div +4 
O_c ch C -- Z3000 Sine -- DVCA -- Mixer ch 2.

Ableton 10 Beta providing gate and drums (generic drum loop from a sample pack), controlled by Novation Launchpad Mini off-screen.  
CVPal Gate -- Branches (60%) -- O_c Trigger
CVPal Gate -- MI Peaks providing envelope to both Ripples VCA (for melody) and DVCA (for bass), ch 2.

title: Harrington Avenue | Eurorack Modular Ambient Downtempo
description:
-- Patch Notes --

Ornament & Crime Harrington 1200 Tune mode, sending pitch to both Braids and Z3000.  Braids routed through and LFO modulated Ripples then to Clouds.  LFO slowly modulating the Freeze parameter.
Ableton sending clock pulses to O_c via CVPal.  Bassline provided by FM8 in Ableton with a Chord to Random Arp.  Drums loop clips in Ableton improvised using a Novation Launchpad Mini.

title: We Are Of Peace | Ambient Eurorack Improv
description:
-- Patch Notes --

Ableton sending a pulse thru CVPal to clock O_c and Temps Utile.
Voice 1: Polyrhythm from Temps Utile sent to Peaks, modulating both Braids and Z3000 w/ different clocks.  Mixer out to 4ms Dual Looping Delay, then Clouds.
Voice 2: Blofeld playing a drone bass, sequenced from Ableton Live with a random arpeggiator.
Drums loops and samples triggered in real time from a Novation Launchpad.

title: particles | z8000 random sequence
description:
z8000 random sequencing 2 voices.  The z8000 is stepping through all 16 steps, while Temps Utile randomly reverses the sequence periodically.  The O_C is quantizing the output from the z8000, sending each step to Plaits and sending every 8th step to Braids for the bass.  Plaits going through Clouds for some sparkle.  Envelopes controlling the filter.  The amount of the filter modulation is controlled by Shades for both voices.
